all_unit_vars = pickle.load(open('1607423454-all_unit_vars.pickle', 'rb'))['data']
for key in all_unit_vars[0].keys():
    unit_vars = list(map(lambda unit_vars : unit_vars[key], all_unit_vars))
    mean_unit_vars = np.mean(np.asarray(unit_vars), axis=0)
    print('Residual units:' if key == 'res' else 'Skip units:')
    indices = np.flip(np.argsort(mean_unit_vars, axis=None))
    # indices = np.argsort(mean_unit_vars, axis=None)
    layer_ids = indices // mean_unit_vars.shape[1]
    channel_ids = indices % mean_unit_vars.shape[1]
    for _, layer_id, channel_id in zip(range(5), layer_ids, channel_ids):
        print('Layer %d, channel %d variance = %f' % (layer_id, channel_id, mean_unit_vars[layer_id, channel_id]))

WaveNet is a deep neural network for generating raw audio. It was created by researchers at London-based artificial intelligence firm DeepMind. The technique, outlined in a paper in September 2016,[1] is able to generate relatively realistic-sounding human-like voices by directly modelling waveforms using a neural network method trained with recordings of real speech. Tests with US English and Mandarin reportedly showed that the system outperforms Google's best existing text-to-speech (TTS) systems, although as of 2016 its text-to-speech synthesis still was less convincing than actual human speech.[2] WaveNet's ability to generate raw waveforms means that it can model any kind of audio, including music.[3]

DPI = 100

def configure_time_axis(ax, num, duration):
    def xformat(value, pos):
        return '%.2f' % (value / num * duration)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.FuncFormatter(xformat))
    ax.set_xlabel('Time (seconds)')
    
def configure_freq_axis(ax, num_bins):
    fmin, fmax = 125, 7600 # from Tacotron2 hparams.py
    mel_to_f = lambda mel : 700 * (np.exp(mel / 1127) - 1)
    f_to_mel = lambda f : 1127 * np.log(1 + f / 700)
    lower_mel = f_to_mel(fmin)
    upper_mel = f_to_mel(fmax)
    
    def yformat(value, pos):
        # value = 1 + value # num_bins - 1 - value
        step = (upper_mel - lower_mel) / num_bins
        mel = lower_mel + value * step
        return '%.2f' % mel_to_f(mel)
    ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.FuncFormatter(yformat))
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency (Hz)')
    
def plot_mel(fig, ax, title, mel):
    num = len(mel)
    duration = num * audio.get_hop_size() / RATE
    configure_time_axis(ax, num, duration)
    configure_freq_axis(ax, mel.shape[1])
    
    ax.set_title(title)
    im = ax.imshow(mel, origin='lower', cmap='coolwarm', aspect='auto')
    fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax)

def display_lc_mel(mel, text=None):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(2, 2))
    title = '' if text is None else '\'%s\'' % text
    plot_mel(fig, ax, title, mel)
    plt.show()


def display_wave(wave, title):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(10,4), dpi=100)
    
    width = RATE // 100
    mid = len(wave) // 2 #int(0.36 * RATE)
    start = mid - width
    end = mid + width
    
    axes[0].set_title('Entire waveform')
    axes[0].set_ylim(-1, 1)
    axes[0].plot(wave)
    configure_time_axis(axes[0], len(wave), len(wave) / RATE)

    ymin, ymax = wave[start:end].min(), wave[start:end].max()
    rec = matplotlib.patches.Rectangle((start, ymin),
                                       end - start,
                                       ymax - ymin,
                                       linewidth=2,
                                       linestyle=':',
                                       edgecolor='r',
                                       facecolor='none',
                                       zorder=3)
    axes[0].add_patch(rec)

    axes[1].set_title('Zoomed in')
    axes[1].plot(wave[start:end])
    configure_time_axis(axes[1], end - start, (end - start) / RATE)#, t0=start/RATE)
    
    fig.suptitle(title, fontsize=14, y=1.01)
    # plt.tight_layout()
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.7)
    plt.show()
    display(Audio(wave, rate=RATE))
    
def center_and_scale_wave(wave):
    wave2 = wave[:]
    wave2 -= np.mean(wave)
    wave2 *= 100
    q = np.quantile(wave2, 1e-3)
    if q != 0:
        wave2 /= q
    return wave2
    
    mean = np.mean(wave)
    std_dev = np.std(wave)
    wave_without_anomalies = wave[:]
    for i, value in enumerate(wave_without_anomalies):
        if np.abs((value - mean) / std_dev) >= 1:
            wave_without_anomalies[i] = 0
    centered_and_scaled_wave = wave[:]
    centered_and_scaled_wave -= np.mean(wave_without_anomalies)
    centered_and_scaled_wave /= np.max(np.abs(wave_without_anomalies))
    return np.clip(centered_and_scaled_wave, -1, 1)

def display_spec(wave):
    # wave, sr = librosa.load(librosa.util.example_audio_file())
    sr = RATE
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10), dpi=DPI)
    D = librosa.amplitude_to_db(librosa.stft(wave), ref=np.max)
    plt.subplot(4, 2, 1)
    librosa.display.specshow(D, y_axis='log')
    plt.colorbar(format='%+2.0f dB')
    plt.title('Log-frequency power spectrogram', y=1.01)
    plt.show()

unit_names = ['skip-layer-1-channel-180']
unit_titles = ['Layer 1 channel 180 skip output']
with open('../text_list.txt') as f:
    texts = f.read().split('\n')[:4]
texts += 3 * [None]

mel_waves = pickle.load(open('1607429424-sounds.pickle', 'rb'))['data'][:4] + 3 * [None]
mel_filenames = ['speech-mel-00001.npy',
                 'speech-mel-00002.npy',
                 'speech-mel-00003.npy',
                 'speech-mel-00004.npy',
                 'diagonal.npy',
                 'straight.npy',
                 'zeros.npy']
mel_base_dir = '../Tacotron-2/tacotron_output/eval'
mel_paths = list(map(lambda filename : mel_base_dir + '/' + filename, mel_filenames))

pickle_paths = os.listdir()
pickle_paths = list(filter(lambda path : path.endswith('.pickle'), pickle_paths))

for unit_name, unit_title in zip(unit_names, unit_titles):
    suffixes = ['-speech0.pickle',
                '-speech1.pickle',
                '-speech2.pickle',
                '-speech3.pickle',
                '-diagonal.pickle',
                '-straight.pickle',
                '-zeros.pickle']
    for text, mel_wave, mel_path, suffix in zip(texts, mel_waves, mel_paths, suffixes):
        mel = np.load(mel_path)
        mel = np.interp(mel, (0, 4), (0, 1))
        mel = np.swapaxes(mel, 0, 1)
        display_lc_mel(mel, text)
        if mel_wave is not None:
            display(Audio(mel_wave, rate=RATE))
        feature_name = unit_name + suffix
        for path in pickle_paths:
            if feature_name in path:
                wave = np.tanh(pickle.load(open(path, 'rb'))['data'])
                wave = center_and_scale_wave(wave)
                # plt.plot(wave)
                # plt.ylim(-1, 1)
                # plt.show()
                # display(Audio(wave, rate=RATE))
                display_wave(wave, unit_title)
                display_spec(wave)
        # break
        print(100 * '=')
